		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Sik wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Yes, you can even make them read all the buttons from a 6-pad if you really want to.</div><br />Do you even need a Genesis/MD for that or can an actual Master System with a Genesis controller do it too?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Just make sure to not do what the Master System port of Sonic Blast does (they moved pausing to the 1 button... WTF? - makes sense in context because on the Game Gear the Start button is a proper polled button and not NMI, but still)</div><br />Since Sonic uses a single action button, I don't think this is such a big problem. I can imagine people who are used to jumping using the button that now pauses being pissed off, but the convenience of being able to pause without getting up is more than welcome IMO. I'm not talking out of laziness, it's more the fact that the time it takes for you to get up and press the button could end up costing you.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
