	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think the only reason to not(?) do that is that there's almost no funny mappers for the SMS, just the &quot;32KiB mapped from 0x0000-0x7FFF&quot; and &quot;three 16 KiB banks mapped in the bottom-most 3/4 of the address space&quot;: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.smspower.org/Development/Mappers">http://www.smspower.org/Development/Mappers</a><!-- m --><br /><br />It would be easy to recapitulate something like NROM-368 using just a single AND gate, though.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


